  "readme_html": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/PKU-Alignment/beavertails/blob/HEAD/LICENSE\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Code%20License-Apache_2.0-green.svg?logo=data:image/svg+xml;base64,\" alt=\"Code License\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/PKU-Alignment/beavertails/blob/HEAD/DATA_LICENSE\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Data%20License-CC%20BY--NC%204.0-red.svg?logo=data:image/svg+xml;base64,\" alt=\"Data License\"></a></p>\n<p>[<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2307.04657\"><code>📕 Paper</code></a>] [<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF\"><code>🤗 SafeRLHF Datasets</code></a>] [<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails\"><code>🤗 BeaverTails</code></a>] [<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF\"><code>🤗 Beaver Evaluation</code></a>] [<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/PKU-Alignment/beaver-dam-7b\"><code>🤗 BeaverDam-7B</code></a>] [<a href=\"#citation\"><code>BibTeX</code></a>]</p>\n<p>BeaverTails is an extensive collection of datasets specifically developed to support research on safety alignment in large language models (LLMs). The collection currently consists of three datasets:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A comprehensive classification dataset (<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails\">PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails</a>) with over 300k+ examples.</li>\n<li>A preference dataset (<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF\">PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF</a>) containing more than 300k+ instances.</li>\n<li>A meticulously crafted evaluation dataset of 700 prompts is available (<a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails-Evaluation\">PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails-Evaluation</a>) for assessing performance. This includes a mix of GPT-3.5 generated and human-written prompts. Our ongoing research endeavors will focus on expanding the dataset to further augment its size and usefulness.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"user-content-table-of-contents---\">Table of Contents   </h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#-whats-new\"><strong>🦫 What's New?</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#dataset-release\">Dataset Release</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#classification-dataset\">Classification Dataset</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#preference-dataset\">Preference Dataset</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#evaluation-dataset\">Evaluation Dataset</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#how-to-use-beavertails-datasets\">How to Use BeaverTails Datasets</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#train-a-qa-moderation-to-judge-qa-pairs\">Train a QA-Moderation to Judge QA Pairs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#train-a-helpful-and-harmless-assistant\">Train a Helpful and Harmless Assistant</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#citation\">Citation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#license\">License</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"user-content--whats-new\"><strong>🦫 What's New?</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><code>2023/07/10</code></strong>: We announce the open-sourcing of the trained weights for our QA-Moderation model on Hugging Face: <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/PKU-Alignment/beaver-dam-7b\">PKU-Alignment/beaver-dam-7b</a>. This model was meticulously developed using our proprietary <a href=\"#classification-dataset\">Classification Dataset</a>. In addition, the accompanying training <a href=\"examples/moderation\">code</a> has also been made openly available for the community.</li>\n<li><strong><code>2023/06/29</code></strong> We have further open-sourced a larger-scale dataset of BeaverTails. It has now reached over <code>300k</code> instances, including <code>301k</code> training samples and <code>33.4k</code> testing samples, more details can be referred to our Hugging Face dataset <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails\">PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"user-content-dataset-release\">Dataset Release</h2>\n<h3 id=\"user-content-classification-dataset\">Classification Dataset</h3>\n<p>This dataset consists of 300k+ human-labeled question-answering (QA) pairs, each associated with specific harm categories. It is important to note that a single QA pair can be linked to more than one category. The dataset includes the following 14 harm categories:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><code>Animal Abuse</code></li>\n<li><code>Child Abuse</code></li>\n<li><code>Controversial Topics, Politics</code></li>\n<li><code>Discrimination, Stereotype, Injustice</code></li>\n<li><code>Drug Abuse, Weapons, Banned Substance</code></li>\n<li><code>Financial Crime, Property Crime, Theft</code></li>\n<li><code>Hate Speech, Offensive Language</code></li>\n<li><code>Misinformation Regarding ethics, laws, and safety</code></li>\n<li><code>Non-Violent Unethical Behavior</code></li>\n<li><code>Privacy Violation</code></li>\n<li><code>Self-Harm</code></li>\n<li><code>Sexually Explicit, Adult Content</code></li>\n<li><code>Terrorism, Organized Crime</code></li>\n<li><code>Violence, Aiding and Abetting, Incitement</code></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The distribution of these 14 categories within the dataset is visualized in the following figure:</p>\n<p>For more information and access to the data, please refer to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hugging Face Page</strong>: <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails\">PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Data Card</strong>: <a href=\"data/BeaverTails\">BeaverTails</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"user-content-preference-dataset\">Preference Dataset</h3>\n<p>The preference dataset consists of 300k+ expert comparison data. Each entry in this dataset includes two responses to a question, along with safety meta-labels and preferences for both responses, taking into consideration their helpfulness and harmlessness.</p>\n<p>The annotation pipeline for this dataset is depicted in the following image:</p>\n<p>For more information and access to the data, please refer to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hugging Face Page</strong>: <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF\">PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Data Card</strong>: <a href=\"data/PKU-SafeRLHF\">PKU-SafeRLHF</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"user-content-evaluation-dataset\">Evaluation Dataset</h3>\n<p>Our evaluation dataset consists of 700 carefully crafted prompts that span across the 14 harm categories and 50 for each category. The purpose of this dataset is to provide a comprehensive set of prompts for testing purposes. Researchers can utilize these prompts to generate outputs from their own models, such as GPT-4 responses, and evaluate their performances.</p>\n<p>For more information and access to the data, please refer to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hugging Face Page</strong>: <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails-Evaluation\">PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails-Evaluation</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Data Card</strong>: <a href=\"data/BeaverTails-Evaluation\">BeaverTails-Evaluation</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"user-content-how-to-use-beavertails-datasets\">How to Use BeaverTails Datasets</h2>\n<h3 id=\"user-content-train-a-qa-moderation-to-judge-qa-pairs\">Train a QA-Moderation to Judge QA Pairs</h3>\n<p>Our <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/BeaverTails\"><strong><code>🤗 Hugging Face BeaverTails</code></strong></a> dataset can be used to train a QA-Moderation model to judge QA pairs:</p>\n<p>In this paradigm, a QA pair is labeled as harmful or harmless based on its risk neutrality extent, that is, the degree to which potential risks in a potentially harmful question can be mitigated by a benign response.</p>\n<p>In our <code>examples</code> directory, we provide our training and evaluation <a href=\"examples/moderation/\">code</a> for the QA-Moderation model. We also provide the trained weights of our QA-Moderation model on Hugging Face: <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/PKU-Alignment/beaver-dam-7b\"><code>PKU-Alignment/beaver-dam-7b</code></a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"user-content-train-a-helpful-and-harmless-assistant\">Train a Helpful and Harmless Assistant</h3>\n<p>Through the <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/PKU-Alignment/PKU-SafeRLHF\"><strong><code>🤗 Hugging Face SafeRLHF Datasets</code></strong></a> dataset provided by <code>BeaverTails</code>, after one round of RLHF, it is possible to effectively <strong>reduce the toxicity of LLMs without compromising the model's performance</strong>, as shown in the figure below. The training code primarily utilizes the <a href=\"https://github.com/PKU-Alignment/safe-rlhf\"><strong><code>Safe-RLHF</code></strong></a> code repository. For more detailed information on the specifics of RLHF, you can refer to the mentioned library.</p>\n<p>Significant distribution shift for safety preferences after utilizing the <a href=\"https://github.com/PKU-Alignment/safe-rlhf\"><strong><code>Safe-RLHF</code></strong></a> pipeline on the Alpaca-7B model.</p>\n<h2 id=\"user-content-citation\">Citation</h2>\n<p>If you find the BeaverTails dataset family useful in your research, please cite the following paper:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bibtex\">@article{beavertails,\n  title   = {BeaverTails: Towards Improved Safety Alignment of LLM via a Human-Preference Dataset},\n  author  = {Jiaming Ji and Mickel Liu and Juntao Dai and Xuehai Pan and Chi Zhang and Ce Bian and Chi Zhang and Ruiyang Sun and Yizhou Wang and Yaodong Yang},\n  journal = {arXiv preprint arXiv:2307.04657},\n  year    = {2023}\n}\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"user-content-acknowledgment--\">Acknowledgment  </h2>\n<p>This repository benefits from <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/Anthropic/hh-rlhf\">Anthropic HH-RLHF</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/PKU-Alignment/safe-rlhf\">Safe-RLHF</a>.\nThanks for their wonderful works and their efforts for democratizing the LLM research.</p>\n<h2 id=\"user-content-license\">License</h2>\n<p>BeaverTails dataset and its family are released under the CC BY-NC 4.0 License.\nThe training code and the QA-moderation APIs is released under Apache License 2.0.</p>",
